Prehistoric man sketched an array of prehistoric beasts on the rough limestone walls of a cave in modern day France 36,000 years ago .
The manmade cavern named the Caverne du Pont-d'Arc in Southern France and contains 1,000 painstakingly-reproduced drawings as well as around 450 bones and other features .
The original ` Grotte Chauvet was discovered around 20 years ago and is a Unesco World Heritage Site .